Feeding an obese child: does not take breakfast and takes cold cuts for dinner
More than a third of children between the ages of 9 and 13 are overweight, 9% of schoolchildren are overweight and 5% are obese.
As current research shows, obese children come from families that have an unhealthy lifestyle.
This shows once again how important the environment in which the human being evolves and the models that surround it.
For example, on the tables of obese children, cured meats are found 50% more often than in families of children with normal weight.
19% of obese people had fries at dinner according to the survey conducted with an awareness campaign "Obesity is not a coincidence"
In the families of the little fats the sport is also not a habit, which is now the case of most of the schoolchildren of today - only 15% answered that at least once a week the parents found time for active movement.
Survey of 900 children
The survey took place during the last school year and involved 900 pupils from primary schools in the Czech Republic.
This was the second edition of "Obesity is not a coincidence", an action supported by the General Health Insurance and the Unilever company.
Since the beginning, more than 12,000 students from sixth to third grade have enrolled in this project.
One of the determining factors that cause a dramatic increase in the number of overweight or even obese children is the lack of a correct diet and not enough physical exercise.
“Only half of the children surveyed reported eating breakfast 5 times a day—in case—lunch—snack—dinner, which is one of the basic principles of a good diet,” one of the survey results said.
No breakfast and cold cuts at dinner
Specialists draw attention to the fact that to have a healthy development you need some basic details such as a family breakfast at the same time.
In the Czech Republic, only 23% of the families of the students eat at the same time.
In most families, everyone eats their breakfast alone.
And the worst thing that has been noted is that one-tenth of the population does not eat breakfast at all.
Breakfast is the basis of a good daily diet.
The questionnaire showed that in families of obese children, unhealthy fries are consumed more often.
Almost every student - not to mention weight - drinks sugary drinks every day (70%).
More than 40% of the children surveyed exercise regularly but for parents it is half, only 15%.
Prepare your food.
Another part of the survey allowed selected children (204 boys and 172 girls from 13 schools) to prepare their own diet from possibilities proposed according to their own taste and personal opinion.
“The preferences of Czech children aged 12 to 15 are far from ideal in terms of healthy eating.”
Among their favorite dishes are lots of cakes, meats and sweets.
"The most alarming is a high preference for sweet lemonades," the survey said.
For lunch it was the pasta that took the first place just in front of the white meat.
The children did not want starches at all and the preference for fish and vegetable meals was very low.
Heading towards health
The survey also showed that children are willing to change their habits from the moment they receive the ad hoc information.
"During a control of a group of survey participants who had filled out the questionnaire after the awareness session "Obesity is not a coincidence", we witnessed a determined desire to move towards a healthy diet," indicate the results of the survey.
The most striking was, for example, when it came to sweet lemonades as children began to give preference to drinking water.
The children most often checked white meat and fish as the main course and would reduce sweet dishes and "knedliky" (Czech specialty of bread or potato dumplings).
