The need for speed The Run is contested throughout America.
Revision
Originally a trouble-free race is transformed because of a set of stupid mistakes of people who have nothing to do with it in a routine morning commute to work.
It fulfills everyone’s ambition to a certain extent, but it is useless if no one wants to do something more.
The new subtitled part The Run produced high expectations before its release.
He promised to take a new direction with the racing series Need for Speed already old and to release a kind of game from playable games that would not count only with points.
So we were curious what the added passages will be like in which the main hero gets out of his car and does whatever he wants.
As is already done in the NFS series, the result is completely different from what was expected.
These are potentially arcade racing games but the whole shoots down because of some unnecessary mistakes that have already existed for several years.
These are not really mistakes but rather the expression of incomprehensible laziness on the part of developers.
The adventure begins very well.
You are caught up in the adventure of which the main hero Jack has character problems and to solve them begins to participate in illegal races throughout America.
You sit behind the wheel on the west coast in San Francisco and your mission is to arrive first in New York.
The idea has interesting elements.
The route is divided into ten stages and then more than 50 races.
As a result, each race takes place on a different route and the stages are planned in different environments that differ quite well from each other and are interesting.
The player does not feel for a single moment that the game offers him something identical.
Some environments are also quite nice even if the graphical technical level is of the same type as the previous series.
This is not the end of the world.
But driving through the desert, in autumnal landscapes or in highly snowy mountains is very visually pleasing.
The events are also occasionally embellished with an atypical element.
For example, in the desert you find yourself in a sandstorm that significantly reduces your visibility.
Then in the mountains you have to be careful that an avalanche does not fall on you.
In addition to this, the different races are well arranged one after the other.
There are only a few, but that is enough.
There are moments when you try to exceed the required number of opponents (as in a classic race) then you run against the clock (classic duel with the stopwatch) and then another duel with an opponent awaits you.
From time to time you also have the police who enter the game and try to make the situation difficult for you.
The novelty is the passages outside the vehicle.
Rather, it’s an interactive animation when most of the time Jack runs away in front of someone and you have to help him by hitting the right button at the right time.
Nothing complicated.
What is surprising is that there are fewer moments of this type than you expect (to be concrete there are only three).
As a result, it is like this because this element is not likely to interfere and is placed, in the context described above, in the elements that embellish the game.
The driving pattern is in the tradition of previous games.
This means that there is nothing extraordinary at the moment, but it cannot be said to be negative.
As for the realistic simulation you will have to go elsewhere.
But although we can find better in the competition the driving model goes very well with the type of design of the races.
So everything is ok.
Problems begin to appear after a while.
In contrast to the driving model, the collision model is not yet at the point.
We don't expect complicated deformation and collisions from this game, but when you don't have, in a collision with any object, the slightest idea of how your car behaves, it's not completely good.
During the tight overtakings you sometimes touch each other slightly but otherwise your self starts in crazy agitations.
Or it ends up in crumbs.
Thanks to the reboot system this is not really a problem but it really annoys you.
The restart is done in such a way that when you have broken your face or you have gone out in the scenery the game brings you back to the moment of the last point on the route.
But you only have 5 reboots.
When you have used the 5 reboots you have to start the game again from the beginning.
So it's more of a tool, in case something doesn't go right, than something you can really count on.
Sometimes the restarts do not help and it is necessary to find the solution by remembering the piece of route in question.
The big draw of this game is that the same actions are found in the same places.
For example, there are certain turns that you have to go through in a certain way otherwise it does not pass.
Otherwise you meet at a given location "civilian" vehicles always in the same configuration as you arrive first, fifth, 5 seconds early or one minute late.
What makes you angry are the situations when you see the opponent easily passing between two cars coming in the opposite direction and when you arrive, you have to either stand aside and circumvent them or brake.
It does not matter if you go ahead of him because it is "calculated" in such a way that for the given situation it always comes very close to your nose.
Opponents have other advantages.
Throughout the game, you arrive in certain places, again without worrying about time, and you always have the same opponent who precedes you in the same place.
This annoys the most at the end of the game when you ride on a long deck in the opposite direction.
The opponent must pass in front of you at all costs.
When it passes in front of you it hides the view of other vehicles in the opposite direction and you collide a good number of times.
It can be understood that the purpose of this game is to do something captivating and full of adredaline, but it is clear that you get bored quickly.
And it's a shame because through a simple driving model the game is interesting and places with so much action that you don't have time to follow everything that happens.
And it doesn’t matter if it’s because of the concept of 50 unique routes, that the order of the races is such that there’s no chance of getting bored or anything else.
The original idea is to change cars during races.
You have to pay attention to the petrol pumps on the routes as you can change cars there however most of the time the one you have is enough for you.
The cars are divided into three categories.
Sports cars are ideal for cities, large American displacements for straight highways and super sports cars with exotic twists on highly technical driving, for example on yawning roads in the mountains.
And the mode of challenges, which are races in particular places that you know from adventure, goes very well with the main scheme of the story.
You receive not only medals but also experience points that add to your profile which is common to challenges and adventure.
When you have reached the highest level of driver, different objects begin to unlock:
It connects online with the Autolog function, which compares your results with those of other players and provides you with other functions in the community.
One of the most difficult moves to understand is the situation of the last race of the adventure.
You arrive with your car in the subway tunnel (it looks like) where you drive in the dark on the tracks (it looks like).
Your speed indicator shows you between 150 and 200 km/h (a priori) and behind you comes a subway train that sends the car directly to the scrap metal.
At the editorial board we had a discussion for a few days about whether someone really thought about it when creating this game or whether the authors really think we're fools.
The technical part of the game is not extra, but the visual part is generally pleasant and in some cases really great.
What bothers me is that in more extreme situations, the imagery does not hold the level and in some cases tragically.
This especially applies to accidents with a large number of participants when fluid imaging is no longer of any use to you.
The sound part is good and the track is choice.
In order to please as many and especially the younger audience as possible, a new soundtrack has been created in the "I mix everything" style, but it can be expected that no one will buy the game for the music.
Need for Speed: The Run is really confusing.
If the game didn’t have these stupid mistakes we could say without fear that it is the best NFS production in recent years.
But this game gives the impression of not being finished.
The fun is really good but be prepared for the mistakes to hit you in the eye with the strength of an aerodrome reflector.
The Velvet Students in concert with the choirs of Charles University
The Festa Academica festival offers for the third time festivities that link the International Student Day with the anniversary of the Velvet Revolution with a musical part.
During the festival there are 20 choirs of the higher schools and secondary classes.
The highlight of the festival is two concerts held on 17 November.
"Charles University has an important part in this festival."
"Among the choirs is the Choir of the Faculty of Pedagogy and Humanities, in the festival committee sits the rector Vaclav Hampl," says the head of the organizing team Jakub Calou.
The highlight of the festival is the concert of the Choir of High Schools and Secondary Schools which takes place with free admission on November 17 from 2 pm on the space located in front of the National Technical Library in Dejvice.
On the program is the composition of the well-known Czech jazzman Karel Ruzicka, Celebration Jazz Mass.
In the evening the concert "Velvet Students" takes place in the premises of the National House in Vinohrady during which the choirs of the higher schools as well as that of Charles University are performed.
The aim of the Festa Academica is not only to celebrate International Student Day with dignity and to commemorate the 22nd anniversary of the velvet revolution, but also to present to the public choir music of the highest level and to develop the creative cooperation of young people.
The main organizer is the Czech Lovers' Union in cooperation with the Jan Kepler High School.
All the action is under the aegis of Bohuslav Svoboda, Mayor of Prague and Vaclav Hampl, Rector of Charles University.
The festival takes place from 16 to 20 November in Prague and Pardubice.
The program offers in addition to high-level concerts, music meetings, student happenings and other activities.
Interested parties will find all the information on the internet pages of the festival www.festaacademica.cz.
Vicenova, Ambassador to the European Union:
Czechs Behave Like Negativists and Eurosceptics
"The Lisbon Treaty has radically removed the balance between the institutions"
“I didn’t expect such a tough war.”
“It will take 5.6 years before the situation calms down and all players get used to their new role,” said the Czech ambassador to the European Union, Milena Vicenova.
When she succeeded in describing the various EU bodies and their relations in such a comprehensible and visible way that a large number of lecturers at Charles University's Faculty of Law might envy her, she showed how much she takes her motto "understandably and openly about Europe" very seriously.
Vicenova paid tribute to the work of Herman Van Rompuye, the new permanent President of the European Council.
“From the beginning, the criticism resounded that he’s dull, that he’s a leatherback, that he can’t fulfill any mission and I have to say that he has taken everyone’s breath away because he plays his part perfectly.”
"He is a man who knows how to listen to 27 member states, communicate well with them and has a clear vision of the direction to take from Europe."
She explained the new post of the High Representative for Foreign Affairs and Defence Policy as part of a response to the question: "Who is who in the European Union?" "Which phone number should I call?", thus as an important step towards the unity and greater readability of the Union's policy vis-<0xC3><0xA0>-vis states, such as China or India.
Nobody wants to forbid us our syrecky (cooked pasta cheese that smells very strong)
Ms Vicenova also mentioned the agenda that the European Council has lived, lives and will live in the near future.
She called the Czech Presidency two years ago a success.
The Czechs have resolved the emerging financial crisis, the gas crisis or organised a Summit for an Eastern Partnership.
She described the fall of the government as very negative and damaged the image of the Czech Republic.
The Czech representation in the EU is currently very busy.
In the words of the Ambassador, "activity has been in full swing" not only for the Presidency but also for the financial crisis that continues to be resolved even now.
The new seven-year budget of the Union, which is becoming very complicated due to the current economic situation, must also be approved.
As it seems that the budget will be thin and with a view to savings, which branch will have priority, which countries will be helped the most, the least, everything is to be resolved in the framework of future negotiations.
The Ambassador recalled her slogans with which she arrived in Brussels "For a comprehensible Europe".
“I really don’t like abbreviations, foreign words, jargon that no one understands.
As the citizen must understand that it is true that in Brussels no one makes round or twisted pickles, bananas differently large or that no one has forbidden us to make syrecky ".
It wants to make better use of the EU environment and see more Czechs in the European institutions.
A multi-speed Europe awaits us
According to the Ambassador, the Czechs have the reputation of being Eurosceptics and people who see things only in their negative aspect more than positively.
In addition, she is sorry to see such a small Czech representation in the European institutions.
According to her, the fault is due to several factors, such as the shyness of our candidates, their inability to write a cover letter and a low level of support from the Czech side.
In addition to a successful Czech Presidency, she then underlined the strength and cooperation of the Visegrad Group.
"Believe me, when the Pole, the Magyar, the Slovak come to me, this Frenchman says to me: 'Hey, what are you doing there, what is this Visegrad group still doing?' and he is not at all happy."
According to Ms Vicenova, in the near future, the Member States are waiting for tough new rules on fiscal policy.
It is the concept of a two-speed, if not multi-speed Europe that prevails rather than a "new European Federation".
“We have countries in the euro zone and others outside the zone.”
"We have the Schengen area, we also have the Institute for Enhanced Cooperation."
In the first place, it was said that countries that want to cooperate with each other and those that do not want to remain in their corners.
"There will be a lot of institutes of this type and there will be a truly two-speed Europe," she said.
From this point of view, it also appreciated the mission of the Czech Republic and Herman Van Rompuye to determine the basis on which all issues having an impact on the EU should be debated among all EU members and not only the members of the Eurozone.
History of a brand:
IBM innovator begins the second century of its existence
If someone were to look for the term that most closely expresses the IBM strategy, the closest would be "the long term".
For a wide audience IBM is the symbol of the technological revolution, is a firm felt as very current and yet since its creation it has been a hundred years.
The foundation of this long-term strategy was laid by the firm’s first chief, visionary Thomas J. Watson Sr.
He left behind the slogan that many global problems can be solved as long as people are willing to think.
Its slogan "Think!" became the imprint around which the life of a future giant will develop (and also the title of the internal magazine that IBM began publishing in 1935).
This was the basis of Watson's care company culture.
For us, IBM means a long-term thought of continuous movements towards the future.
IBM survived a hundred years because it always remained true to its core values and yet was not afraid to change everyone else around it.
This has enabled us during our first century to transform technology, business and society.
We hope that in the second century we will reach even more"delayed for the anniversary the current director of the firm Samuel J. Palmisano.
A well-prepared system
Watson, in the 1930s, began taking care of his employees like Bata in the Czech Republic - the people of IBM were the only ones among the first American employees to have paid vacations, insurance paid by the employer plus an elegant employee uniform and a well-developed system of rewards for inventors and dealers.
In the same way IBM has a well-developed customer relationship system.
The company was initially great at discovering talent – as one of the first firms to have abolished all forms of discrimination and thus had a choice.
The current plan is completely in the spirit of the anti-discrimination strategy since it will be a woman – Virginia Rometty – who should replace Palmisano at the head of IBM.
