We didn't know much about each other, but we did invent a little thing that could control big things. It was an incredible lesson, and I don't think Apple would have existed without it.
Steve Jobs continues by telling a wonderful tour that he and Wozniak have devised: he phoned the Vatican with the Blue Box in the middle of the night posing as Henry Kissinger and asked to speak to the Pope.
